00:48:23.500 --> 00:48:26.710
that will go up ideally
3x over three years or 4x.

00:48:26.710 --> 00:48:29.580
Just very, very large
movements in price.

00:48:29.580 --> 00:48:31.980
And I am blown away
by the number of times

00:48:31.980 --> 00:48:34.670
that I, who at the time
thought he was rational,

00:48:34.670 --> 00:48:37.280
I now know better,
would be dissuaded

00:48:37.280 --> 00:48:39.640
by the price
movement on the day.

00:48:39.640 --> 00:48:44.905
So the thing is priced at
10 and we know in retrospect

00:48:44.905 --> 00:48:47.890
that it was going to go
to 50 and I didn't buy it

00:48:47.890 --> 00:48:50.930
because it was training
up by two, by two basis

00:48:50.930 --> 00:48:53.000
points or something, and
that really impacts you,

00:48:53.000 --> 00:48:54.030
and it's crazy.

00:48:54.030 --> 00:48:57.070
So there's a-- I found
that it's just simpler.

00:48:57.070 --> 00:49:00.110
And it's actually,
it's not I found,

00:49:00.110 --> 00:49:02.000
I learned it directly
from Mohnish Pabrai.

00:49:02.000 --> 00:49:04.550
He showed me the rule and it
was obvious to me the minute

00:49:04.550 --> 00:49:05.570
he said it.

00:49:05.570 --> 00:49:08.700
Just don't allow yourself to
trade when the markets open.

00:49:08.700 --> 00:49:11.020
Decide the night before
what you're going to do

00:49:11.020 --> 00:49:12.150
and then put the trade in.

00:49:12.150 --> 00:49:13.524
Decide-- I mean,
the debt doesn't

00:49:13.524 --> 00:49:15.840
mean you shouldn't put limit
orders in or find some way

00:49:15.840 --> 00:49:20.380
to make sure that-- but think
about it in a quiet environment

00:49:20.380 --> 00:49:22.330
and then, and then
allow it to happen.

00:49:22.330 --> 00:49:24.680
And--

