So I say, so Warren, I want
to put you in these shoes.

01:01:25.260 --> 01:01:28.180
I'm a manager of yours
and I come to you.

01:01:28.180 --> 01:01:31.330
And I'm a manager of a
substantial business of yours

01:01:31.330 --> 01:01:35.600
and you rely on my performance
for the success of Berkshire

01:01:35.600 --> 01:01:38.280
Hathaway and I come to
you with a confession.

01:01:38.280 --> 01:01:42.430
And I say, I'm deeply envious
of a peer in my industry

01:01:42.430 --> 01:01:44.130
and it's just eating me up.

01:01:44.130 --> 01:01:46.690
And I know that
it's going to force

01:01:46.690 --> 01:01:48.465
me, get me to make
decisions that are not

01:01:48.465 --> 01:01:51.100
good for the business, but
what do I do with this envy?

01:01:51.100 --> 01:01:54.112
And I'm hoping for pearls of
wisdom to fall from heaven

01:01:54.112 --> 01:01:55.820
and I said, so what
would you say to him?

01:01:55.820 --> 01:01:57.657
And he's like, I don't know.

01:01:57.657 --> 01:02:02.980
[LAUGHTER]

01:02:02.980 --> 01:02:04.950
And I don't know where
I, I, I got this from.

01:02:04.950 --> 01:02:07.100
He did talk to us about
this inner scorecard

01:02:07.100 --> 01:02:09.270
idea at the lunch extensively.

01:02:09.270 --> 01:02:12.120
And just so that you know
it, for those of you who

01:02:12.120 --> 01:02:14.440
don't want to buy the book,
which I totally understand,

01:02:14.440 --> 01:02:18.190
he says-- there are many
books out there-- he says,

01:02:18.190 --> 01:02:20.750
would you rather be
considered by the world

01:02:20.750 --> 01:02:22.880
to be the best
lover in the world,

01:02:22.880 --> 01:02:24.820
but between you and
your wife to know

01:02:24.820 --> 01:02:27.250
that you really suck,
or would you rather

01:02:27.250 --> 01:02:29.660
for the world to think that
you're pretty bad at being

01:02:29.660 --> 01:02:31.280
a lover, but for
you and your wife

01:02:31.280 --> 01:02:32.930
to know that you're
the very best?

01:02:32.930 --> 01:02:35.010
And obviously that
was a distinction

01:02:35.010 --> 01:02:37.670
that I had not really
fully understood and made.

01:02:37.670 --> 01:02:40.110
And it was really hard
for me, because I realized

01:02:40.110 --> 01:02:44.040
how much of my life I'd lived
by an external scorecard

01:02:44.040 --> 01:02:46.100
and I realized in
writing the book

01:02:46.100 --> 01:02:51.270
how much of the environment that
we all operate in is so-- exam

01:02:51.270 --> 01:02:54.620
results, all sorts
of evaluations.

01:02:54.620 --> 01:02:57.510
Those are all in a certain
way, in many cases,

01:02:57.510 --> 01:02:59.110
external scorecard.

01:02:59.110 --> 01:03:02.060
And I was telling Sarab that my
children are in a Montessori,

01:03:02.060 --> 01:03:03.989
Montessori school right now.

01:03:03.989 --> 01:03:06.280
I think maybe one of the big
things that the Montessori

01:03:06.280 --> 01:03:08.655
school system does is it
teaches you, and in a scorecard,

01:03:08.655 --> 01:03:12.110
it teaches you to focus on the
things that give you true joy.

01:03:12.110 --> 01:03:14.730
But I'll tell you what
really does deal with envy,

01:03:14.730 --> 01:03:19.090
and this works, is that,
a really powerful idea,

01:03:19.090 --> 01:03:20.840
emotions are a call to action.

01:03:20.840 --> 01:03:24.690
So anger is an, is an indication
that your boundaries have been

01:03:24.690 --> 01:03:27.350
violated, so you need to
protect your boundaries.

01:03:27.350 --> 01:03:30.940
For example, being
sad and being in pain

01:03:30.940 --> 01:03:34.090
means that you need to
seek nurture and security.

01:03:34.090 --> 01:03:38.290
Envy is a signal-- so
the misdirection of envy

01:03:38.290 --> 01:03:44.100
is, I hate that guy I want
his life, and I don't have it.

01:03:44.100 --> 01:03:46.215
And so that's envy.

01:03:46.215 --> 01:03:48.340
And I don't know why it's
associated with the color

01:03:48.340 --> 01:03:49.440
green.

01:03:49.440 --> 01:03:52.750
The call to action is there's
something wrong in my life

01:03:52.750 --> 01:03:54.560
that I need to change.

01:03:54.560 --> 01:03:58.990
And I promise you,
example, the morning

01:03:58.990 --> 01:04:02.690
I woke up next to my wife,
totally in love with her,

01:04:02.690 --> 01:04:04.910
having had an
extraordinary night.

01:04:04.910 --> 01:04:06.660
I was not envious of anyone.

01:04:06.660 --> 01:04:08.000
My life was really good.

01:04:08.000 --> 01:04:11.410
The days that I've spent
on a windsurfer, yeah,

01:04:11.410 --> 01:04:14.720
just surfing those waves, with
a blue sky and strong wind,

01:04:14.720 --> 01:04:16.120
I was not envious of anyone.

01:04:16.120 --> 01:04:18.860
You could give me Bill
Gates, Warren Buffett, Steven

01:04:18.860 --> 01:04:20.370
Spielberg, you name it.

01:04:20.370 --> 01:04:22.620
When you're in those
moments you're not envious.

01:04:22.620 --> 01:04:26.456
So I think that, what I came
away from that lunch was,

01:04:26.456 --> 01:04:29.490
increased recognition
of my own envy,

01:04:29.490 --> 01:04:33.440
and increased recognition
of how much my life was

01:04:33.440 --> 01:04:37.400
on an external scorecard,
and the absolute desire

01:04:37.400 --> 01:04:37.960
to change it.

01:04:37.960 --> 01:04:39.660
And for me that meant
leaving New York.

01:04:39.660 --> 01:04:41.909
I realized that New York
wasn't a healthy place to me.

01:04:41.909 --> 01:04:44.530
So I think there is a
way to deal with envy.

01:04:44.530 --> 01:04:47.270
It's fixing what--
fixing-- ensuring

01:04:47.270 --> 01:04:49.320
that we go to bed every
night happy with what

01:04:49.320 --> 01:04:50.820
we did during the day.

01:04:50.820 --> 01:04:52.340
And if we're not
doing that, then we

01:04:52.340 --> 01:04:54.152
need to try really
hard to get to a place

01:04:54.152 --> 01:04:55.110
where we're doing that.

01:04:55.110 --> 01:04:58.160
And once we're doing that
we won't have any envy.

01:04:58.160 --> 01:04:59.840
So thank you all for coming.

01:04:59.840 --> 01:05:03.790
I hope I, I hope I [INAUDIBLE].

